peech about the civil rights act under consideration passed  pdf neglected voices new york university school of law archived from the original pdf on october   retrieved october     joseph rainey archived  at the wayback machine black history month national treasury employees union  mark m smith “all is not quiet in our hellish county’ facts fiction politics and race – the ellenton riot of ” south carolina historical magazine vol  no  april  – at jstor subscription required  melinda meeks hennessy “racial violence during reconstruction the  riots in charleston and cainhoy” south carolina historical magazine vol  no  april  – at jstor subscription required further readingedit packwood cyril outerbridge  detour—bermuda destination—us house of representatives the life of joseph hayne rainey hamilton bermuda baxters  ”joseph hayne rainey” in black americans in congress – office of history  preservation u s house of representatives washington government printing office  holt thomas “rainey joseph hayne” in dictionary of american negro biography edited by rayford w logan and michael r winston new york norton and co  external linksedit wikiquote has quotations related to joseph hayne rainey congressional biography at the biographical directory of the united states congress connecticut freedom trail official website joseph rainey dec   speech about the civil rights act under consideration passed  neglected voices nyu school of law joseph rainey picture history photos us house of representatives preceded by benjamin f whittemore member of the us house of representatives from south carolinas st congressional district – succeeded by john s richardson retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlejosephraineyoldid categories  births deathsafricanamerican members of the united states house of representativesafricanamerican state legislators in south carolinaamerican slavesamerican people of french descentamerican people of haitian descentbarbersmembers of the united states hou